<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1690,2041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1726,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Pleomere 6 1.2 times as long as wide. Telson 1 times as long as wide; greatest width 1.2 times posterior width. Maxilliped 3 ischium-merus 3 times as long as wide; merus free distal margin oblique. Female major cheliped ischium lower margin with 4 strong spines; merus lower margin with simple proximal spine; palm 1 times as long as carpus. Uropodal endopod anterior margin with small spine about two-thirds along.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,987,1870,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1690,2041]" box="[199,987,1870,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1870,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Distribution.</emphasis>
