<typeStatus box="[608,656,1871,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Andaman Sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1690,2041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1907,1933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[323,468,1906,1933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" pagination="1431 - 1467" refId="ref11995" refString="Sakai, K. (2010) Callianassoidea from the Gulf of Tonkin and the Red sea, in the Zoological Museum of Moscow University (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana, 83, 1431 - 1467. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 001121610 X 538174" type="journal article" year="2010">Sakai (2010)</bibRefCitation>
reidentified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, 2010:" authorityYear="1438" box="[643,911,1906,1932]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Trypaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamaniensis">
<emphasis box="[643,911,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Trypaea andamaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from the Andaman Sea first identified by him as 
<emphasis box="[319,564,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grebenjuk" authorityYear="1975" box="[319,560,1942,1968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinae">Callianassa tonkinae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The uropod, telson and maxilliped 3 appear identical to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bate" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1297,1436,1942,1969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinae">
<emphasis box="[1297,1436,1942,1969]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">S. amboinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the female cheliped is more robust and with a stronger more proximal meral spine. A juvenile male was reported without pleopod 1 and with a bi-articulate pleopod 2 (cf. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ngoc-Ho" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[791,942,2014,2041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis box="[791,942,2014,2041]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">S. caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai &amp; Poore &amp; Fujita, 2020" authorityName="Komai &amp; Poore &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2020" box="[956,1068,2015,2041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[956,1068,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">S. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1075,1138,2015,2041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1075,1138,2015,2041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
